  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6836",
  "title": "Add `exports.types` to the package.json of `react-instantsearch`",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nHi. We were trying out the [new beta native TS compiler (`@typescript/native-preview`)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@typescript/native-preview), and the only error we are getting is to do with `react-instantsearch`:\n\n```\nerror TS7016: Could not find a declaration file for module 'react-instantsearch'. '/Users/marcel/Code/owid-grapher/node_modules/react-instantsearch/dist/cjs/index.js' implicitly has an 'any' type.\n  Try `npm i --save-dev @types/react-instantsearch` if it exists or add a new declaration (.d.ts) file containing `declare module 'react-instantsearch';`\n\n2 import { Snippet } from \"react-instantsearch\"\n```\n\nI have confirmed that this simple change to `react-instantsearch`'s package.json makes the issue go away:\n```diff\n@@ -8,6 +8,7 @@\n   \"type\": \"module\",\n   \"exports\": {\n     \".\": {\n+      \"types\": \"./dist/es/index.d.ts\",\n       \"import\": \"./dist/es/index.js\",\n       \"require\": \"./dist/cjs/index.js\"\n     }\n```\n\nAfaict, this shouldn't negatively affect anything else.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a package that imports `react-instantsearch`\n2. Run `npx @typescript/native-preview -b` on it\n\n### Live reproduction\n\n--\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\n--\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch 4.20.2\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
